---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/en/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/en/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="PRIVACY POLICY | Privacy Policy">
  <div class="bg-white text-[#483F38]">
    <Header />

    <main>
      <!-- Privacy Policy Main (SP 기준) -->
      <section class="privacy-policy-section bg-[#FAFAFA] pb-[80px] lg:pt-[222px] lg:pb-[150px] lg:px-[256px]">
        <div class="flex w-full flex-col items-center gap-[40px] font-['Shippori_Mincho'] px-[16px] lg:px-0 lg:gap-[80px]">
          <div class="contents">
          <h1 class="m-0 text-center text-[32px] leading-[48px] tracking-[3.6px] font-medium text-[#436C5E] lg:mx-auto lg:w-[616px] lg:text-[36px] lg:leading-[54px]">
              <span class="lg:hidden">Privacy Policy</span>
              <span class="hidden lg:inline">Privacy Policy</span>
            </h1>
            <div class="policy-body w-full text-[14px] leading-[22.75px] tracking-[2.1px] text-[#475569] lg:text-[16px] lg:leading-[32px] lg:tracking-[1px]">
              <p>
                aoshima tei SUZU – SUZU – (the "Company") establishes this Privacy Policy (the "Policy") regarding the handling of users' personal information in the services provided on this website (the "Service").
              </p>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 1 (Personal Information)</h2>
              <p class="mt-[8px]">
                "Personal information" means information about a living individual as defined in the Act on the Protection of Personal Information, which can identify a specific individual by name, date of birth, address, telephone number, contact information, or other descriptions, as well as data such as appearance, fingerprints, voiceprints, and insurer numbers on health insurance cards (personal identification information) that can identify a specific individual by itself.
              </p>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 2 (How We Collect Personal Information)</h2>
              <p class="mt-[8px]">
                The Company may ask users for personal information such as name, date of birth, address, telephone number, email address, bank account number, credit card number, and driver's license number when registering for use. The Company may also collect transaction records and payment information containing users' personal information from partners such as information providers, introducers, travel arrangers, affiliated partners, and package operators (collectively, "Partners").
              </p>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 3 (Purpose of Collection and Use)</h2>
              <p class="mt-[8px]">
                The purposes for which the Company collects and uses personal information are as follows. We will not use personal information beyond these purposes without the user's consent.
              </p>
              <ol class="policy-list-decimal mt-[8px] space-y-[2px]">
                <li>To provide and operate the Company's services and handle related matters</li>
                <li>To respond to user inquiries (including identity verification)</li>
                <li>To send emails about products, services, updates, events, campaigns, and other business activities offered by the Company</li>
                <li>To contact users as necessary regarding maintenance and important notices</li>
                <li>To identify users who violate the Terms of Use or attempt to use the Service for fraudulent or improper purposes, and to refuse their use</li>
                <li>To exercise rights or fulfill obligations under applicable laws and regulations</li>
                <li>To analyze facility usage for the purpose of improving products and services</li>
                <li>To bill users for service fees</li>
                <li>Purposes incidental to the above</li>
              </ol>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 4 (Changes to Purpose of Use)</h2>
              <ol class="policy-list-decimal mt-[8px] space-y-[2px]">
                <li>The Company may change the purpose of use of personal information only when the new purpose is reasonably related to the previous purpose.</li>
                <li>If the purpose of use is changed, the Company will notify users or publish the updated purpose on this website in accordance with the Company's prescribed method.</li>
              </ol>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 5 (Provision to Third Parties)</h2>
              <ol class="policy-list-decimal mt-[8px] space-y-[6px]">
                <li>
                  The Company will not provide personal information to third parties without obtaining the user's prior consent, except in the following cases or as permitted under the Act on the Protection of Personal Information and other laws.
                  <ul class="policy-list-circle mt-[8px] space-y-[2px]">
                    <li>When it is necessary to protect the life, body, or property of a person and it is difficult to obtain the individual's consent</li>
                    <li>When it is particularly necessary for improving public health or promoting the sound growth of children and it is difficult to obtain the individual's consent</li>
                    <li>When it is necessary to cooperate with a national or local government agency or its delegate in performing duties prescribed by law, and obtaining consent may impede the performance of such duties</li>
                    <li>
                      When the Company has notified or publicly announced the following matters in advance and submitted a notification to the Personal Information Protection Commission
                      <ol class="policy-list-decimal mt-[6px] space-y-[2px]">
                        <li>That the purpose of use includes provision to third parties</li>
                        <li>Items of data to be provided to third parties</li>
                        <li>Means or method of provision to third parties</li>
                        <li>That the Company will stop providing personal information to third parties upon the user's request</li>
                        <li>How to accept such requests</li>
                      </ol>
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  Notwithstanding the preceding paragraph, the following cases shall not constitute provision to a third party:
                  <ul class="policy-list-circle mt-[8px] space-y-[2px]">
                    <li>When the Company entrusts all or part of the handling of personal information within the scope necessary to achieve the purpose of use</li>
                    <li>When personal information is provided in connection with business succession due to merger or other reasons</li>
                    <li>When personal information is jointly used with a specific party, and the user is notified in advance or is able to easily know the items, scope of joint users, purpose of use, and the name of the person responsible for management</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ol>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 6 (Management of Personal Information)</h2>
              <p class="mt-[8px]">
                The Company will appropriately manage personal information and take reasonable technical measures to prevent unauthorized access, loss, destruction, alteration, or leakage. We will continuously improve these measures, keep personal information accurate and up to date to the extent necessary for the purpose of use, and appropriately supervise personnel handling such information.
              </p>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 7 (Disclosure of Personal Information)</h2>
              <ol class="policy-list-decimal mt-[8px] space-y-[6px]">
                <li>
                  If a user requests disclosure of personal information, the Company will disclose it without delay. However, if disclosure falls under any of the following cases, all or part of the information may not be disclosed, and the Company will notify the user of such decision without delay. A fee of 1,000 JPY will be charged per disclosure request.
                  <ul class="policy-list-circle mt-[8px] space-y-[2px]">
                    <li>When it may harm the life, body, property, or other rights or interests of the user or a third party</li>
                    <li>When it may seriously impede the proper execution of the Company's business</li>
                    <li>When it would violate laws or regulations</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Notwithstanding the preceding paragraph, the Company will not disclose information other than personal information, such as history or characteristic information, in principle.</li>
              </ol>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 8 (Correction and Deletion of Personal Information)</h2>
              <ol class="policy-list-decimal mt-[8px] space-y-[2px]">
                <li>If a user finds that the Company's personal information is incorrect, the user may request correction, addition, or deletion ("Correction, etc.") in accordance with the Company's procedures.</li>
                <li>If the Company deems it necessary to respond to such request, it will promptly perform the Correction, etc.</li>
                <li>The Company will promptly notify the user of the decision to perform or not perform the Correction, etc.</li>
              </ol>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 9 (Suspension of Use, etc.)</h2>
              <ol class="policy-list-decimal mt-[8px] space-y-[2px]">
                <li>If a user requests suspension or deletion ("Suspension, etc.") of personal information on the grounds that it is handled beyond the purpose of use or was obtained by improper means, the Company will promptly conduct the necessary investigation.</li>
                <li>Based on the results of the investigation, if the Company deems it necessary to comply with the request, it will promptly perform the Suspension, etc.</li>
                <li>The Company will promptly notify the user of the decision to perform or not perform the Suspension, etc.</li>
                <li>Notwithstanding the preceding paragraphs, if Suspension, etc. involves excessive cost or is otherwise difficult, the Company will take alternative measures necessary to protect the user's rights and interests.</li>
              </ol>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 10 (Changes to Privacy Policy)</h2>
              <ol class="policy-list-decimal mt-[8px] space-y-[2px]">
                <li>The contents of this Policy may be changed without notice to users, except as otherwise provided by laws or this Policy.</li>
                <li>Unless otherwise specified by the Company, the revised Policy will take effect when posted on this website.</li>
              </ol>

              <h2 class="mt-[24px] font-medium text-[#111827]">Article 11 (Contact)</h2>
              <p class="mt-[8px]">For inquiries regarding this Policy, please contact the following office.</p>
              <div class="mt-[8px] space-y-[4px]">
                <p>3523 Co., Ltd. (aoshima tei SUZU – SUZU – Operations Office)</p>
                <p>889-2162 4-48-4 Aoshima, Miyazaki-shi, Miyazaki</p>
                <p>Tel: 0985-73-8555</p>
                <p>info@3523.jp</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a href="/en/" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-[#B99563] bg-[#B99563] px-[49px] py-[10px] text-[14px] leading-[22.75px] tracking-[2.1px] text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-[#B99563] hover:border-[#B99563] transition-all duration-300">
            <span class="lg:hidden">TOP</span>
            <span class="hidden lg:inline">Back</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
  <style>
    .policy-list-decimal {
      list-style-type: decimal;
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
    }

    .policy-list-circle {
      list-style-type: circle;
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
    }

    .policy-list-decimal li,
    .policy-list-circle li {
      padding-left: 0.15rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 1023px) {
      .privacy-policy-section {
        padding-top: calc(var(--header-height, 72px) + 80px);
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
